reviewText: I love this movie and was surprised to learn that it was produced on such a low budget. The quality of the end product says a lot for the producers, director, photographers and cast. I am HUGE on graphics and love the graphics in this movie. Congrats to the entire cast and crew, especially to producers Ed Polgardy and Scott Rudolph. Highly recommended in DVD. ♥
summary: Gave me goosebumps...without the blood and gore... My kind of horror!

reviewText: Worst movie I have seen in a long time. Even though we paid for it, we turned it off after 30 minutes instead of wasting more of our lives.  Acting was non- existent and cinematography was high school/home video level at best. Special effects were not even in the last decade of movie magics. If I could I would not give it any stars.

reviewText: A fairly entertaining flick under the "don't mess with the black arts" heading. You end up not liking any of the people involved in this story. They are all quite willing to screw each other over in order to misuse the artifact for their own reasons. And in the end, they all get what they deserve.
